      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vivian is a proud pixie, and there's nothing she wants more than to trounce her academic rival, Anne. But when an unexpected opportunity arises, a series of unfortunate mishaps lead to the tables being turned on her. What will Anne do then, with her pretty little fairy?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1262315-will-she-punish-me/chapter/1262318/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Oneshot&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/83534/meteorologist/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/20/ava_83534_1709267912.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/83534/meteorologist/"&gt;Meteorologist&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Content warnings: &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="sp-wrap sp-wrap-default"&gt; &lt;div class="sp-head" title="Expand"&gt; Spoiler &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="sp-body folded"&gt; &lt;p&gt;This story contains sex between a pixie girl and a penis-having woman. There will be magic stretchiness, so if that sounds gross to you, don't read.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="spdiv"&gt;[collapse]&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Chatter filled the classroom, even as our professor – Mrs. Baer – walked to the front, ready to begin her lecture. We’d all supposedly grown up already, had our Class awakenings and – at least those of us who were lucky enough – been sent off to University free of charge, but just as my size had never increased, neither had the maturity of my classmates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I shot dirty looks to both sides of me, crossing my arms to match my legs below me on the surface of my desk. My bright pink skin kneaded itself into the scratched and worn wood, my irritated energy needing to go &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;somewhere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;, and I’d already learned what happened when I let that energy go to the translucent wings sticking regally out of my back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My neighbor, the ever-present Anne, leaned over towards me and whispered, “Hey Vi, if you’re so horny that you’re fucking your desk you should probably go–”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Shut up!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;” I hissed, “And it’s Vivian.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She held up her hands in mock surrender, her wavy, boyish hair bouncing on the top of her head at the gesture. “Okay, jeez – I don’t think you need any more V’s to your name, but…” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A snicker from one of her many hanger-ons sounded out from the row behind us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Thankfully, our scrap was finally ended by Mrs. Baer clearing her throat and rapping her knuckles on the hard wood of the podium she stood behind. The couple dozen students slowly quieted down and shushed each other, and her booming voice echoed across the room, bouncing off the posters showing detailed anatomical sketches of everything from dragons to gargoyles. My favourite illustration was of a slime, at least half of which was taken up by an empty circular blob.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Alright,” the professor started, “Today we’re going to be reviewing team dynamics and group strategy, and that’s because…” she trailed off dramatically, the fuzzy rounded ears atop her head twitching in excitement, “It’s finally time for your first unsupervised excursion!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A few half-hearted woo’s answered her. It was hard for any of us to get excited after three years of brutal studying and training – all the while being told in excruciating detail all of the ways we could die when we finally did our first assignment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Now, I’m sure you’re all excited, and given the way I’ve been hammering teamwork, it’ll come as no surprise that you’ll be in groups.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I glanced around the room, dreading the prospect of working with any of the clowns around me. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Mrs. Baer continued, striding across the front of the room with mock-pensiveness. “Unfortunately, some of you have… differing abilities, and special care needs to be taken with your team composition. As such, not all of you will be able to pick your teams.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My eyes instinctually moved towards Anne – a prime example of someone who’d surely earned the privilege of choosing her own team, and unlike me, had plenty of people to choose – although I never understood what the women constantly clinging to her and fighting for her attention saw in her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“The parties I have chosen are posted at the door. Please check them on the way out, even if you think your name isn’t there.” Her strides brought her back to behind her podium, where she leaned forwards, the sturdy furniture creaking under the weight of her strength. “Now, let’s continue with the lesson. First up is support abilities…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I tuned out as she began her lecture. Not only was it review, but, like every class other than ‘physical development’, I was in the top two. Of course, before we’d gotten our Classes, mine being &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Pixie Artillery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;, I’d been top &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;one&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; in those same classes, despite the fact that my rival had gone to the same school as I. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I didn’t know what Anne’s Class was, or how it allowed her to go from a middling nerdy human boy to a popular, effortlessly smart, and devastatingly fit catgirl but I knew if I wanted to take the lead in Mrs. Baer’s class, I needed to dramatically outperform her on the assignment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Not that that would be easy, given that the whip she’d dominated our grade’s spars with weighed almost as much as my whole body. I was at a significant disadvantage in person-on-person combat given my stature and how little I trusted the people around me to guard me like my Class demanded. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Every time I’d faced off against Anne in team spars, she’d corner me, single-handedly hunting me down regardless of terrain, and press the thick base of her whip against my neck, pinning me down as the leathery material dragged against my soft skin. She’d lord over me with that infuriating smirk of hers and ask me to submit to her – as per the rules of the spar – and, having no other choice, I would.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;For this assignment, however, I could let loose and ignore my teammates since the creatures we were hunting wouldn't know the little pink thing was actually a fearsome sorceress the way my classmates did.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Once Mrs. Baer finished her lecture and dismissed us, I got up and flew past my classmates, cavernous gaps opening up between them as they noticed me, torn between their fear of my wrath and their eagerness to find out if they were on the professor’s shitlist. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I filtered past the desks and lazily scanned the sheet, hovering so that it was eye-level for me, instead of being three feet above me like if I’d been standing on the ground. Anne, the only one brave enough to approach me, peered over my shoulder, her eyes likely scanning for the names of her harem more than her own name.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;At the bottom, below all of those who were struggling, instead of the belated relief I’d expected, I found something as horrible as it was strange.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Special Assignment: Anne Baker and Vivian Willow (see me after class)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Shit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;,” I cursed, flitting back towards Mrs. Baer’s desk and ignoring Anne’s husky chuckle as she followed behind me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And why is it just the two of us? Couldn’t she at least have given us one of your bitches so I didn’t have to talk to you?” I whined, flying under a low-hanging tree branch and pulling it along with me for a moment before letting it whip behind me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Anne dodged with a slight movement of her head, just as used to my pranks as she was my complaining by now. We’d only been on the road for a few hours – long enough to escape any sign of civilization, but not long enough to be close to our destination – and I’d already gone through each of my annoyances at being paired with her three times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’d appreciate it if you didn’t disparage my girlfriends,” her voice was bored, matching her expression, even as her thin black tail twitched angrily behind her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Two of them are &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;literally &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;part dog,” I insisted, referring to the women that had canine ears and tails, “And don’t call them your girlfriends as if you’re all equals – at best they’re your harem, and at worst your Class lets you somehow keep sex slaves in plain sight and no one but me thinks to question it.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Anne’s tail yanked itself straight before slowly curling in on itself again. She muttered to herself, “&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The fuck is she talking about, sex slaves…?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;” Her scoff disappeared, masking itself as a sadistic grin as she rebounded, instead going on the offensive, “Oh, I already knew you were inexperienced, but are you really so much of a prude that healthy relationships are scary to you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m not &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;prudish&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;.” My hands brushed over the outfit I was wearing, an admittedly covering tunic and tights combo, “I’m just wary of perverts.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh,” she let out, her ears drooping atop her head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A long, awkward silence stretched out, where I had plenty of time to myself to move on with my thoughts, leaving her odd reaction behind me. It was easier said than done, however.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Why, after all of the mean things we’ve said to each other, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;that&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; was what got to her? Usually it’s just her harem she’s protective of, and she doesn’t care what I say about her…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And why does she look so &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;sad&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My head flicked back after every tree trunk I had to skirt around, my constantly fluttering wings letting me subtly glance at her. Anne was living up to her cat side, putting on a show of being a pouty kitten while ambling behind me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She expects me to believe that act? I bet if I apologize to her, she’d just make fun of me – not that I want to apologize to her in the first place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I continued forwards, my dodges becoming more frequent as the trees grew denser, the shadows running longer and thickening as the sun went down and the tension in the atmosphere refused to dissipate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We made camp soon after, and of course since Anne had to carry the supplies – even if the magic bags made it lighter and less bulky, I couldn’t carry a tent – I didn’t get a tent of my own, nor did I get a bedroll of my own.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Normally, in this kind of situation, I’d expect her to endlessly tease me, making pointed comments about the sheer negligee I wore to bed with that smirk of hers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Instead, given that the tension between us remained unresolved, my wear went uncommented on, leaving me feeling unfulfilled as I laid down on the packed earth, only the thin fabric of the tent cushioning me below and the corner of Anne’s blanket above protecting me from the elements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I mumbled a goodnight to her – the first words exchanged between us since she’d stopped us to make camp – but she only grunted in response.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So what’s the plan?” I asked, circling around Anne’s head as she batted branches out of her face, stumbling through the foliage by the scarce morning light.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She ignored me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hmm, it’s kind of hard for me to make plans on my own, especially when I don’t know shit about your Class…” I floated by her head, miming laying down on my side, my hand propping up my head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her ears twitched, but still no response came.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Honestly it’s irresponsible not to share more details about your Class – sure you get the privilege of being secretive about it when we’re rivals, but teammates? I could be in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;danger&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;For a moment it seemed like she wasn’t going to crack, until she whipped her hand out, clipping my leg and sending me careening into a dangling branch thick with moss. “&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Shut up&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;,” she fumed, before continuing her silent march forward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I rubbed my leg, thankful for the soft moss that’d caught me, and once again feeling bitter about the tension between us. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But it’s an act – she’s just trying to make fun of me again, right?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Maybe I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;should &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;apologize…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Instead of following that thought anywhere, I buried it, joining Anne in her fuming all the way to our destination. By the time we’d gotten to the outside of the cave that was the site of our assignment, it was about time for our second camp, although given that we’d skipped lunch in our mutual stubbornness, we were slightly ahead of schedule. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We went through the same silent routine, Anne setting up the tent and cooking the two of us food – her portion an order of magnitude larger than mine – while I set up the magical defences, taking extra care because of how close we were to the beasts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I nibbled through my meal, glancing at Anne’s blank expression every so often, and it seemed like the night would end the same way as the previous, until she finally spoke. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’re right, you know.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wha?” I let out unconsciously, shocked she’d even spoken in the first place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She set down her bowl, the surface already clean of sauce. “I’m a pervert. You know it, I know it, the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; know it…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Piecing together bits of context, I winced. “Your Class?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her face turned away, the edge of her cheek I could still see a brighter pink than even my skin. “Forget it.” And then she stood and moved to stalk into the woods surrounding us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I flew past her, stopping in front of her face with my arms stretched wide. “No, you don’t get to escape from me like that – let’s talk.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She shook her head, “I just need to get some buffs done for tomorrow and we can go to bed.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Just buff in front of me?” I tilted my head, trying to figure out what could be so embarrassing or perverted about buffs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well no, it’s…” Anne stammered. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I darted forward, leaning my face closer to hers, “It’s what?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I need to orgasm every night to get a buff the next day!” she belted out, her red face staring at the floor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...” I blinked silently.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I couldn’t do it last night without bothering you, so I was a bit grumpy this morning – I’m sorry for hitting you…” she shuf