      <pubDate>Wed, 25 Sep 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dylan is a 17 year old boy, living in a small town in Michigan. He's heavily bullied, not just by kids at school, but even by his own parents, who blame his shortcomings on his size and lack of devotion to Christianity. One day, while drawing down by the local river, he's attacked by a group of bullies. During the attack, he's saved by a mysterious girl, who sends them packing! Before he can thank her, she runs off.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Later that week, he joins one of his only friends for a game of D&amp;D at the local game store, against his parents wishes. There, he finds that the girl who saved him is actually the DM of the group! Not only that, but she's actually a boy as well! Together, the two venture down paths Dylan had never dreamed of before!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1234705-dungeons-and-dresses/chapter/1234738/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1: Summer Blues&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_news"&gt; &lt;div class="wi_news_title"&gt;&lt;i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle" aria-hidden="true" style="padding-right:5px;"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Announcement&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_news_body"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Content Warning: This story involves depictions of depression, bullying and physical assault. Reader discretion is highly advised.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Another summer vacation had come and gone, and a new school year was set to begin. Why had it flown by so quickly? So many comfortable days, walking in the forest, sitting by the river, just enjoying nature, now replaced by textbooks, desks and walls. Oh how I wished I could just leave it all behind. To walk into nature and never return. After all, what did school ever do for me? Nothing but stuffy classrooms and horrible people. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;If there was any saving grace, it was that this was my last year of it. Come next summer, I’d never have to think about it again. Unfortunately, there were 10 long months between then and now. I wondered if I would even survive that long? My parents were certainly no help. Dad kept insisting I needed to “put some meat on my bones and bulk up”, but that was the last thing I wanted. Mom always said there was no future in art, which was about the only talent I had. So what was the use in trying? Not like I’d ever amount to anything anyways.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Since today was officially the last day of summer vacation, I decided to take one last trip down to the river in the local park. I made sure to wait until both of my parents had left for work, before reaching into my hiding spot and pulling out my sketchbook. I had saved up my allowance to buy it, it was my most precious possession. The one thing in my life that brought me any real sort of joy! I hugged it close to my chest, grabbed my backpack and headed out on my bicycle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Black Oak Falls was a pretty ordinary town, with schools, banks, offices, restaurants, etc. and overall just boring. But just on the edge of town stood a beautiful forest! I happened to know it really well, as I spent a lot of time out there. I could just sit out on a stump for hours, sketching all I could see. It was so relaxing, and good to be away from people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I hated people, more than anything else in this world. Not just how they destroyed nature and ruined our planet for the sake of greed, but also because they were mostly assholes. I did have one or two people I called friends, they were nice to me. But my parents only saw me as a disappointment, and I was relentlessly bullied at school. No one really seemed to care about it. Teachers ignored me, my parents hated me and the other kids were of no help. I really was alone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I soon arrived down at the river. It wasn’t far from downtown, but I purposefully always took a dirt path further down river, deep into the park. There was less chance of running into anyone there. I parked my bike and sat down on the riverbank. Finally, a chance to relax. I took out my sketchbook and started drawing. I wanted to capture how the river flowed, and the plants that grew around it. Maybe if I was lucky, I’d even see a fish jumping out of the water!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After a while of relaxing and sketching, my ears picked up familiar sounding voices nearby. My eyes quickly shot up as my worst fears were confirmed. Frank, Joey and Rodney, all of them went to my school, and they were all bullies. Frank was the leader, a tall jock from the school’s basketball team. Joey was the muscle, and held back 2 years from graduating. Finally there was Rodney, I didn’t know much about him. He never said a word, but did as Frank told him. The worst part of it all? I was their favorite target.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I quickly got up to leave when Frank spotted me. “Well if it isn’t Dispshit! Where you been hiding all summer, Dispshit?” he asked in a very sarcastic tone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Leave me alone Frank, I’m not bothering you. And my name is Dylan!” I said, trying to brush them off.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Not so fast, Dipshit. It seems you’ve stumbled onto our little secret!” he said as I noticed a joint in his hand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s none of my business where you 3 go to make out, now leave me alone!” I said sarcastically.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;That seemed to just piss him off. “What did you just say you little freak?!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Maybe you haven’t heard, it’s ok to be gay these days! Go enjoy your little threesome, I won’t tell anyone!” I shot back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That does it! Joey, grab him!” he barked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I tried to run for it, but Joey was on me before I could get more than a few feet away. He tackled me to the ground, causing the contents of my backpack to spill on the ground. Frank walked over, making sure to step on my sketch pencils, as he picked up my sketchbook.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well well, what do you got here Dipshit?” he said, flipping through my work. “Do you fancy yourself some kind of artist?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hey! Give that back!” I shouted, struggling to get free from Joey’s grasp.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I don’t think so. See, I think there should be some kind of punishment for intruding on our little hideout here, as well as that big mouth of yours. And I know just how to do that!” he smirked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I struggled helplessly as he walked over to the edge of the river, sketchbook in hand. One by one, he ripped out the pages and threw them into the water! All my hard work, carelessly thrown away like garbage! Tears began to form in my eyes, I had to stop this somehow!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Put it down you fucking jerk!” I shouted at him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Frank just looked at me and smiled that horrible smile. “Well, if you insist,” he said as he dropped the whole sketchbook into the river!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Noooo!!!” I shouted as I finally squirmed free! I ran straight over to the water, but of course, I was too late. The sketchbook was already making its way down the river. I broke down in sobs. I had bought that book with my own money! I’d saved up for months, just to be able to afford it! And now it was gone!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Frank laughed, which made Joey laugh. Rodney just stood there, stoically, not making a sound. “Aww, look at the little crybaby!” Frank said in a mocking tone. “Does the baby want his wittle book back?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I turned and glared at him. An uncontrollable rage took me over as I ran over and punched him with all the strength I could muster! It caught him off guard as I knocked the wind out of him. Before I could manage to throw another punch, Rodney grabbed me from behind, as Joey ran over to Frank.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You ok boss?” Joey asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m fine,” he managed to get out. “Never mind me, it’s time to teach this loser a lesson!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;With that, Frank and Joey turned their attention to me. I tried to free myself once more, but Rodney had my arms well and truly pinned behind my back. Joey came over and landed a punch, square in my gut! My eyes went wide as I felt all the air exit my lungs at once! I started coughing, trying to breathe. Frank took this opportunity to kick me, right between the legs! I let out a high pitched shriek of pain, Rodney let go as I fell to the ground. I couldn’t move after that!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As they started kicking me on the ground, a voice called out: “Hey! Why don’t you pick on someone your own size?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The trio looked over and saw a girl standing there. “Walk away girly, this don’t concern you,” Frank said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Maybe you didn’t hear me the first time, I said leave that poor kid alone and pick on someone your own size!” she said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What are you gonna do about it?” Frank asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Without hesitation, she ran over and punched him square in the jaw! It caught everyone off guard, watching Rodney fall to the ground with blood starting to trickle down his chin. He was stunned, did a girl just kick his ass? No way in hell he was gonna let her get away with that!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Joey, Rodney, what are you bozos waiting for? Get her!” Frank shouted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The two of them snapped out of their stupor and went after her, with Joey being close enough to get to her first. However, faster than he could blink, she used his own momentum against him and flipped him to the ground! It was a hard landing. Rodney, clearly enraged by this, went and took a swing at her. Swiftly, she dodged his fist and landed an elbow straight into the square of his back! He dropped like a sack of potatoes. Finally, Frank was back on his feet and came charging at her with his shoulder, like a linebacker going for a tackle. The girl simply sidestepped him and stuck her foot out, causing him to lose his balance and fall face first into the ground!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The girl looked down at him and smirked, “How’s the ground taste?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Frank just growled. “We ain’t gonna stand for this! Next time we see you, you’re toast! Come on guys, let’s go.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;With that, the three of them took off, presumably to lick their wounds. I was amazed, this girl had just come out of nowhere to save me! Now that I had a chance to breathe, I could get a good look at her. She was absolutely beautiful! Her long, golden hair was tied up in a braid on the back of her head with a pink ribbon that matched the dress she was wearing. While the dress was a bit scuffed, I couldn’t help but admire the design. A mix of pink and white with slightly puffed sleeves and a skirt that came down just above her knees. Her feet were simply clad in white tennis shoes, but somehow, it really fit her aesthetic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She held out a hand to me, which let me see her long nails, painted the same shade of pink as her dress. “Hey, are you ok? Let me help you up,” she said with a light smile, emphasizing the makeup on her face.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I quietly took her hand and slowly got up. Everything was hurting, but somehow, looking at her made me feel better. Something was stirring in me, but it was hard to focus through the pain. Just as I was about to open my mouth to thank her and ask her name, there was a chime that came from her direction. To my surprise, she pulled a cell phone out of the pocket of her dress. Could dresses even have pockets? That was news to me! I’d always heard my mom complain about that.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hello?” she said, answering her phone. “Oh, hey auntie … Uh huh … Oh crap, uh, yeah, I’m just picking it up now … Yeah, I’ll see you soon. Bye bye,” and with that, she hung up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She looked at me apologetically. “Sorry, I gotta run. I was actually on my way to get dinner for me and my aunt! It was nice meeting you, hope you’re ok!” She gave me a quick kiss on the cheek before taking off running!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I just stood there, stunned. The prettiest girl I’d ever seen had not only just saved me from Frank and his gang, but also kissed me! I was enamored with her. Who was this girl? Wait, she hadn’t even told me her name! How would I find her again? I was pretty sure I hadn’t seen her at school before, I’d remember a face like that. But without more information, it was unlikely I’d see her again. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I sighed. This sucked! First girl I’d ever met that had a crush on and she was likely gone for good! I just had to resign myself to my fate. And with my sketchbook gone, there was nothing left for me to do out there. Reluctantly, I grabbed my bike and headed for home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A while later, I got home. It hurt too much to ride my bike, so I walked the whole way. It was a long walk, made even longer with all the pain. Still, somehow I made it back. Though I was completely exhausted and hurting all over. I laid down on the couch to rest for a little while and the next thing I knew, I was waking up to my dad coming in the door. This was gonna be a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; conversation. I groaned as I got up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hi Dad,” I managed to get out, trying to sound cheerful.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He took one look at me and his face turned sour. “What happened this time?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nothing, I’m fine!” I lied.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He just sighed. “You’re absolutely filthy and covered in bruises. You’re not fine. Son, what have I told you? You’re almost 18, and you’re thin as a rail. You need to put some meat on those bones, get in shape! You’ll never find a woman who’ll marry you like this. You’ll be alone for the rest of your life and never have kids of your own. Do you think that’s what God’s plan is for you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;In that moment, I wanted to get angry. I wanted to yell and scream at him, ask him what the fuck was wrong with him! Here I was, completely beaten up, and all he could do was scold me?! What kind of father does that? He didn’t even bother to ask if I was ok! No, apparently in his world, it was my own fault I got my ass kicked for the crime of minding my own business! I did nothing, yet apparently because I was weak, I deserved it! What kind of bullshit was that?!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But instead of saying any of that, all I could get out was a weak, “Sorry Dad…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He shook his head. “Just go get cleaned up before your mother gets home.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Without another word, I went upstairs to take a shower. I turned the water on and stepped in. From there, I just sat down and cried. This sucked, I hated this, I hated &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;him&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;! What was the point of any of this? Of carrying on this way? No one cared about me, no one would be sad if I was gone. I was completely alone, even my friends were just casual ones. They didn’t really care much about me. I was rarely invited to anything, even when I was a kid. Hangouts, birthday parties, stuff like that, I was usually only invited out of obligation. What was wrong with me?!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After spending about a half hour in the shower, I got out and dried off. Despite being 17, I still had limited access to the internet. My parents insisted I was too young to be online without strict parental controls. That included the family computer and my cell phone. Luckily for me, I had a solution for that. I went back to my hiding spot, a loose floorboard behind my bed, and pulled out my second phone. This one was prepaid, just had to be updated with a fresh phone card every month. The downside was that the data was fairly slow, and I only got 5GB per month. Still, my parents didn’t know about this one so I had a way to privately browse the internet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As I watched some Youtube videos with crappy earphones to mask the sound, the phone rang, making me nearly jump out of my skin! I checked the caller ID, it was the one person I trusted enough to give this number to, my closest friend TJ. I quietly answered. “Hey TJ, what gives? I told you only to call me if it was important! I can’t let my parents find this phone.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Sorry man, just needed to ask you something. Saturday, me and some friends are doing D&amp;amp;D down at the game store, but we’re short a player. Wanna join us?” TJ asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“D&amp;amp;D? You mean that Dungeons and Dragons game? You know I can’t do that, my parents will never let me go! Besides, I wouldn’t even know how to play. Sorry, you’ll have to find someone else,” I said, though I felt bad. I did want to go, I just couldn’t risk it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Come on, you’re always making excuses! Your folks never approve of anything. Not me, not your art, not anyone from school! Why is this any different? Live a little, have some fun with me and the rest of the group. It’s either that or you sit at home and do nothing. Choice is yours,” he said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I thought about it for a moment. Did I really wanna spend another night, wallowing in my own misery at home? Especially now, without my sketchbook, it would be pretty boring. Maybe I should try living a little for once like he said!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Alright fine, I’m in. But you’re gonna have to teach me how to play. I wouldn’t even know where to start!” I said, trying not to get too excited over this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Deal. Meet me downtown on Saturday, by the pizza place. You know the one. I’ll get you in the game shop without your parents or any of their church friends ever seeing you. Trust me, alright?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I trust you TJ, thank you. I’ll see you at school tomorrow,” I said as I hung up.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;For once, I had plans! Real, legitimate plans! I was still nervous, could I really get in unseen? And what would I tell my parents? They believed D&amp;amp;D was evil! Their mindset was stuck in the 1980s, that D&amp;amp;D was “evil” and “Satanic”. During my secret internet time, I’d looked up what’s now known as the “Satanic Panic” of the 1980s and 90s. Basically, during this time, games like D&amp;amp;D were gaining in popularity while accusations of Satan worship were on the rise. People legitimately believed these games were being used to summon demons and stuff, and that “human sacrifices” were being made in these rituals! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Of course, none of this was true. Some assholes made up some bullshit and people believed it! Some weird kind of therapy was being used to find “hidden memories” of ritualistic abuse of kids. Problem was, it wasn’t actually happening and these therapists were actually leading people to find these memories, whether they were real or not. Of course religious groups latched onto this as well, including my parents’ church. They believed strongly in this, which led to me being pretty isolated from anyone who wasn’t part of that church.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This is partly why I was such an outcast. As a kid, I was never allowed to get into more pop culture stuff. Pokemon, anime, anything like that was strictly off limits because it was “Satanic”. I could only watch or play with things they approved of. Which was mostly either educational or religious content. It was SOOOO boring, but what choice did I have? They were my parents, they controlled this stuff. I had to go along with it. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But as I approached adulthood, I wanted freedom. Which is something they refused to let me have. They always insisted I was “too young” and all that stuff because of my birthday. Yes, technically I was born on February 29th, but that didn’t stop me from actually getting older! I wasn’t a child anymore! I was 17, whether they liked it or not! I was more than old enough to have some measures of freedom! I couldn’t wait until I finally turned 18. Hopefully these next six months would just fly by and I could find a way to get out of here. Somewhere far away, where I could make a fresh start.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Before long, Mom arrived home. I turned off my secret phone and put it back in its hiding spot. The last thing I wanted was to get caught and have them take it away. I threw on a t-shirt and shorts and sighed. I never liked my clothes. They always felt like they were gonna fall off me, they were so baggy! Or at least, that’s how I imagined them. Something about them always felt so loose, like I was being shoved in a bag every time I put them on. I wanted something tighter fitting, but I could never tell my parents. They would think it was too weird or something. I really didn't wanna deal with it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I plastered on a fake smile and went downstairs. I was still hurting but hopefully, after that shower, my injuries would be less noticeable. Mom and Dad were talking in the kitchen, though I didn't pay too much attention to what was being said. After a minute, Mom looked over and saw me, turning her attention my way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Your father told me what happened,” she started.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What? I just, fell. That’s all. I was out riding my bike and I fell. No big deal.” I lied, trying to sound nonchalant about it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“God detests liars you know,” she said, staring a hole through me. “This is the 4th time in the last two months you’ve come home injured like this! Why can’t you learn to stand up for yourself? After all, the Lord helps those who help themselves. If you just stand up to those bullies, you’ll have God on your side!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Fat lot of good that’ll do,” I muttered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What was that?” she snapped.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I said, how am I supposed to stand up for myself? As Dad keeps pointing out, I got no muscles. It was 3 on 1, those assholes had me cornered! What was I supposed to do exactly?” I replied.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Watch your language young man! You don’t need to use force against them, just stand up for yourself. Tell them you’re tired of being bullied all the time and they should back off. If they’re reasonable young men, they should listen,” Mom said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I couldn’t help but laugh at this. “Oh sure, that’ll totally work! Why didn’t I think of that? Telling them to go away, it’s brilliant! Thank you so much Mom!” I said with heavy sarcasm in my voice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Don’t take that tone with me! How would you like to spend the rest of the night in your room, with no dinner?” she threatened.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Let me get this straight then. I get beaten up, you blame me for it, and now because I’m standing up for myself, like you told me to, I don’t get to eat? Does that sound right to you?” I asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Don’t talk to your mother like that!” Dad snapped.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Why not? She told me to stand up for myself! Isn’t that what I’m doing?” I said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We are your parents, not some schoolyard bullies! You should give us the respect we deserve! Do as we tell you!” He was getting red in the face at this point.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Whatever. I’ll just be in my room, not eating. Have fun pretending I don’t exist!” I said as I stormed off back upstairs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I was pissed as I slammed my bedroom door behind me! It was the same old bullshit and I was tired of it! They always blamed me for shit that wasn’t my fault! Always said I should rely on God or whatever, but what good has He ever done for me?! I was alone with two shitty parents, who believed their faith was more important than me! If He doesn’t make mistakes, like they claimed, why was I stuck with them? Someone had to screw up somewhere here!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I once again went into my hiding spot and pulled out a bag of chips and some cookies. This was my emergency stash of food, just in case of something like this. It wasn’t much, and the cookies were kinda stale, but it would quell my rumbling stomach for the moment. As I laid on my bed, munching on chips, I thought about everything that happened. From the bullies attacking me, to my parents blaming me, but most importantly, that girl.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Just who was she? Why did she save me like that? Did she have some beef with Frank and his goons? It certainly wasn’t for my benefit, I’d never even met her before! And yet, I wanted to meet her again. After all, I hadn’t even gotten a chance to thank her, let alone get her name! But the thing that stood out to me the most for some reason, was her looks. That dress, that hair, even her makeup! It was all so pretty! I was almost jealous!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Wait, jealous? Why would I be jealous of a girl? That was a weird thought. I had no reason to be jealous of how pretty she looked! Especially not that, gorgeous dress she was wearing, or how her makeup perfectly suited her face… I was violently pulled from my thoughts by a knock at the door! I quickly hid the snacks and brushed away any visible crumbs. I looked over as the door opened, revealing my mom with a plate of food in her hands. “Hi sweetheart, mind if I come in?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Do what you want I guess,” I replied, coldly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She came in and sat down on my bed. “I’m sorry we were so hard on you earlier. We just want you to be the best man you can be. A man of God. That’s why we want you to stand up for yourself, to get bigger. You’re practically underweight! It would do you a lot of good to get some meat on your bones, like your father wants. It’s all part of God’s plan! We realized sending you to your room with no dinner was a mistake on our part. You can’t grow big and strong without proper nutrition! So here, I made you a plate. You can eat here if you’d like. We just want what’s best for you, that’s all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I was so tempted to roll my eyes at that. It was such a backhanded apology, and as usual, treating me like a little kid! But on the other hand, those chips weren’t exactly filling. So it was for the best to play along for the moment so I could at least have some pork chops!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I understand Mom, but I would at least like some sympathy here. I didn’t do anything and I was attacked, then it felt like I was being attacked again here because you and Dad blamed me for it! Can you blame me for getting mad about it?” I said, hoping to get her to see things my way, at least a little.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m sorry you feel that way, we weren’t trying to blame you at all. We simply want to help you to be a good man! So we’re gonna push you a little. The world is not a very kind place, you need to have the strength to endure it. Your father and I won’t be around to help you forever, God will call us home eventually. You need to become strong enough to live on your own one day! If you can’t deal with a group like this, what chance do you have out in the world?” Mom said, trying to sound reassuring.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I just sighed. There was no getting through to her, clearly. I gave it a good try, but she wasn’t gonna listen. “Whatever you say Mom, I’ll try to be stronger. Can I eat before my food gets cold?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Of course dear, enjoy your dinner,” she smiled as she sat the plate down. She gave me a kiss on the head before leaving the room and headed back downstairs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Without much else to do, I ate my dinner. There was at least one thing I could give my parents, they did make good food without trying to be overly healthy. Pork chops with mashed potatoes and peas, which made for a decently balanced meal. So I just enjoyed this small comfort while I could. Hopefully this weekend would bring better times…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After a long few days of school, Saturday finally rolled around. I just needed to get out of the house and meet TJ down by the pizza shop. Shouldn’t be too hard, right? After showering and getting dressed, I headed downstairs. My parents were sitting in the kitchen, eating breakfast.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Morning Dylan, you’re up early,” Mom said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, I know. I got plans today,” I responded honestly, hoping they wouldn’t dig too deep.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh? What kind of plans?” Dad chimed in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ah, I’m just going to see TJ and hang out for a while. Maybe get some pizza downtown, nothing major,” I said, which was a half truth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“TJ? Hmm, do we know him?” Dad asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We’ve known each other since middle school, you’ve met him a couple times,” I said, a bit annoyed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh yes, him. He seems like a decent kid. You’re not gonna get into any trouble, are you?” he said, with a bit of a knowing tone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nah, probably gonna walk around town a bit, maybe go to his place, pretty uneventful really. Pizza will probably be the highlight of it all,” I said, just trying to end the conversation before I had to dig myself in too deep.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Alright, well you have fun dear. Be home by dark!” Mom said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Mom, come on, aren’t I a little old for such an early curfew? I don’t wanna have to rush home just cause the sun is starting to set. I can handle being out late!” I complained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Keep it up and I’ll make it by 5 instead,” she said, sternly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ugh, fine! I’ll try to be home by dark. Can I go now?” I groaned.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Aren’t you gonna have breakfast first?” Dad asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nah, I’ll get something to eat while I’m out. I’m good. I really gotta go, he’s expecting me soon!” I was getting antsy at this point, it felt like the barrage of questions would never end!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well, alright. Have a good day then son,” Dad said. And with that, I was out the door!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I could not get out of that house fast enough, it was worse than prison! At least there, you get 3 square meals a day, access to a tv and even non-religious books! It had to be better than what they put me through on a daily basis! I grabbed my bike and headed downtown. I actually had some time to kill, but wanted to get out of the house as fast as possible! I made my way to the local bakery, they usually had some good stuff I could get for fairly cheap. I think the owners probably felt sorry for me or something, cause sometimes they’d give me food for free.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Once I had some food in my stomach, I waited for TJ to show up. I checked my phone, I still had about a half hour before our arranged time. I figured this would be a good chance to get a lay of the land, so to speak. So I locked up my bike and walked around, making sure to keep my distance from the game store. Last thing I wanted was anyone seeing me around the place and telling my folks. They were leaders at their church, so everyone there knew them, as well as me by association. One too many times, someone had seen me doing something that was “inappropriate” and reported it to them, causing me to get in trouble. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;So I had to play it safe. I walked across the street from the store, and sure enough, there was a pizza place next door. Pizza Orbit it was called, because it orbited Galaxy Games and most of its customer base was from there. Hungry nerds with a few bucks to blow on some pizza, quite the business model if you ask me. I’d gone by this place many times before, but never had I actually gone inside. When I was a kid, I believed the stupid shit my parents told me about it being a front for Satan worshipers. Now though? That ranks as one of the dumbest things I’ve ever heard! It’s just a bunch of nerds playing games together!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As I was staring at the place, lost in my own thoughts, I felt a tap on my shoulder. I must have jumped at least a mile into the air! I looked back to see TJ nearly falling to the ground, he was laughing so hard! He was a big guy, standing at about 5’10, and weighing nearly 300 pounds! To most people, he’d seem kind of intimidating, but to me, he was my friend. My friend who was about to get an earful for scaring me!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Dude! Not cool!” I said, trying to regain my composure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh come on, you should have seen yourself! I swear you were about to touch the stratosphere, you jumped so high!” He continued laughing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I rolled my eyes. “Yeah yeah, yuck it up! You just caught me with my guard down, that’s all!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He finally caught his breath, but still had a goofy smile on his face, “I’m glad you made it man, been looking to introduce you to the gang!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Right, if you say so. You said you could get me in without being seen?” I asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Absolutely! Just follow me and keep quiet, no one will ever know! Trust me!” He said with full confidence. It made me wanna trust him, so I did.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I followed TJ into Pizza Orbit. Why were we here exactly? Was this where we were meeting his friends?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He walked up to the counter. “Hey there, I’d like the manager special please,” he said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The worker looked at him. “Right, just a moment,” and they walked off. A minute later, a familiar looking woman, who seemed to be the manager, walked out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hey little bro, good to see you!” she said, smiling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hi sis, nice to see you too. You remember Dylan, right?” he asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She looked over at me. “Oh yes, I remember! Nice to see you Dylan!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It was TJ’s older sister, Isabelle! I’d seen her the few times I’d been over to his house when we were younger. Last I had heard, she was off in college! What was she doing back in this sleepy town?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So what’s up? You want me to hook you up with some free food or something? Cause you know I can’t do that,” she asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nah, I was actually hoping you could let us take a shortcut through the kitchen and head out the back. We’re trying to get over to Galaxy Games, through the back door. You know how Dylan’s parents are,” he said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ahh, cute little plan you got here. Alright, I’ll help you out, but don’t touch anything! Got it?” she said sternly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I promise,” TJ said, crossing his heart.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I promise too, I just wanna get through without being seen,” I chimed in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Alright, I’m trusting you two. Come with me,” she said as she went through the door to the back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;TJ and I quickly followed behind her, as she walked us through the kitchen. Luckily, the place wasn’t that big, so we arrived at the back door in almost no time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Here, go out here and it’ll take you to the back of Galaxy Games. Honestly, I didn’t even know people who don’t work there could go in that way. But if anyone asks, this didn’t happen. I’m not gonna lose this job over helping you two, understood?” she said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Of course sis, my lips are sealed. See ya at home later,” TJ said as the two of us walked towards the game store.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Once we got over there, TJ knocked four times on the door rhythmically. The door opened slightly and a voice was heard on the other side. “What is the password, knave?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;TJ rolled his eyes. “How should I know? You keep changing it!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What were the famous last words of the last campaign?” the voice asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;TJ thought for a moment, before realization came over his face! “Oh! The password is: ‘we got this’!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The voice didn’t say another word. Instead, the door closed. I thought that was it, he’d gotten the password wrong! But a moment later, it opened again, fully this time! The two of us went inside. TJ looked at the guy who had been behind the door. “Do we have to do this song and dance every week Brett? I did the knock, you should know it’s me by now!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“The password is more fun,” the man, now known as Brett, said with a grin. “So is this the guy you said would be filling the last spot for our campaign?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That’s right, this is Dylan. Dylan, this is Brett. He’s one of our fellow players and he works here at the shop,” TJ said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s nice to meet you Brett,” I said, a bit nervous. I wasn’t really good around new people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Same with you Dylan, welcome!” he said with a smile. “I hope you enjoy your time here!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Come on, let me introduce you to the rest of the group,” TJ said, as he led me into the room.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;First up was an Asian girl, she looked a bit younger than me, about the same height, but with a very large chest. I absentmindedly scratched my chest while looking at her. She came over. “Well, look at what the cat dragged in, nya,” she said with a bit of an accent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Heh, hi Lilly, good to see you too. Dylan, this is Lilly, or LLS as we call her,” TJ said, introducing her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“LLS? What does that mean?” I asked, now curious.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Lucky Little Shit,” Lilly said, laughing. “I get a lot of high rolls and they swear my dice are loaded. But I’m just a silly little kitty!” she pouted and held her hands up under her chin like cat paws.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ah, so the new sacrifice has arrived! Welcome!” came a voice from across the room.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I turned towards the source of the voice and my jaw just about hit the floor! Sitting at the head of the table, wearing a black, metal band t-shirt with a white skirt, was the same girl who had saved me the other day! She must have recognized me too, cause she had a similar look on her face! She got up from her chair and walked over to me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I, is it really you?” I managed to stutter out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Without a word, she came over and hugged me! “It’s so good to see you again! I’m glad you’re ok! Have you had any more trouble with those assholes?” she asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Everyone in the room stared at us. This was a level of familiarity I wasn’t expecting! “I, I’m fine. Frank and his crew haven’t come near me since you kicked their asses. I wasn’t expecting to see you again, not after you just ran off like that!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, sorry about that. My aunt was waiting on me. I tried taking a shortcut through the park and well, shit happens, you know?” the girl said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I had no idea you two knew each other already,” TJ interjected. “That should make things easier. This is the DM, or dungeon master, for our group! He tries to keep us idiots in line!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;HE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;?!” I asked, looking at what seemed to be obviously a girl in front of me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh right, I never did get to introduce myself. Yeah, I’m Bobby. I’m actually a guy, I just prefer wearing girls clothes and stuff. You’re Dylan, right? Good to formally meet ya!” Bobby said, holding out his hand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I was in complete shock! The girl who had rescued me was actually a guy? But, she, he was so pretty! I couldn’t wrap my head around it! TJ put his hand on my shoulder. “Don’t worry, it’s always a bit of a shock at first, but you’ll get used to it,” he said.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Alright, now that everyone’s here, we can get started!” Bobby announced as he went back to his chair. Everyone else went and took seats at the table, so I took the remaining empty seat. This was gonna be an interesting day…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Chapter 1 End&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_news"&gt; &lt;div class="wi_news_title"&gt;&lt;i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle" aria-hidden="true" style="padding-right:5px;"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Announcement&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_news_body"&gt;Welcome to a brand new story! After my small bout of burnout, I needed to work on something fresh. I've had this idea in my back pocket for a while, loosely based on a dream I had! The D&amp;amp;D backdrop wasn't originally part of it, but an idea that came up in planning. I needed a catchy title, and when I jokingly said Dungeons and Dresses to my team, they loved it! So I decided to roll with it, despite having no experience with the game myself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There's a lot I could say about this story, but I'm more curious, what do you think so far? Where do you think this is gonna go? If you know me, the path should be fairly predictable, but I wanted a slow burn. Leave your thoughts and predictions in the comments!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
