      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;"O, Daughter of the Air,&lt;br /&gt; Unbound to the earth,&lt;br /&gt; Head chained to the clouds,&lt;br /&gt; Cursed to dream."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Adam has always felt drawn to girls. I mean, what guy wouldn't? That's normal, right? Especially when you're stuck at an all-boys boarding school, curiosity is inevitable. They're just so fascinating in a way, and pretty too. Something that deserves admiring, even if only from afar. A part of him wishes he could do even more, that in some other world he could even... no, that thought was silly. Forget that. It was stupid to think about. Besides, he already has his share of duties and responsibilities to the people around him, between his friends, his tutor, choir practice, even his grandfather who happened to be the Headmaster. Yes, that's right. Making everyone happy was more important.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Though when he notices a boyish looking student attending the all girls school close by, he finds himself fixated, and his mind wanders further. There's just this weird feeling he can't place. What was it? Why does it all become harder to ignore the more he thinks about it? Just what if... What if this painful desire buried inside, was actually possible? One might think it would take magic...&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Does a happy ending await one who wants what they can't have?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
